The OnTrack CLI (`ontrack`) is a full-featured command-line interface for route optimization.

## Installation

```bash
# Via Nix
nix run github:qompassai/Python#ontrack-cli

# Build from source
cd ontrack-rs
cargo build --release
# Binary: target/release/ontrack
```

## Commands

### `ontrack route` — Optimize a Route

```bash
# From a CSV file
ontrack route stops.csv

# Interactive mode — type addresses one per line
ontrack route --interactive

# With options
ontrack route stops.csv \
  --backend osrm \
  --solver 2opt \
  --depot 0 \
  --open-maps \
  --export route.csv
```

**Flags:**

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--backend` | `osrm` | Distance matrix: `osrm`, `google`, `haversine` |
| `--solver` | `2opt` | TSP algorithm: `2opt`, `nn` |
| `--depot` | `0` | Starting stop index |
| `--open-maps` | off | Open route in Google Maps |
| `--open-fieldmaps` | off | Open first stop in ArcGIS FieldMaps |
| `--open-waze` | off | Open first stop in Waze |
| `--export FILE` | none | Export route to CSV |
| `--open-route` | `true` | Open route (don't return to start) |
| `--interactive` | off | Enter addresses interactively |

### `ontrack geocode` — Geocode Addresses

```bash
ontrack geocode "123 Main St, Madison, WI" "456 Oak Ave, Madison, WI"
```

Prints lat/lng for each address. Useful for verifying geocoding accuracy.

### `ontrack location` — Current Location

```bash
ontrack location
```

Shows approximate device location via IP geolocation.

### `ontrack config` — Show Configuration

```bash
ontrack config
```

Displays current `.env` settings (API keys, OSRM URL, etc.).

## Global Flags

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `-v, --verbose` | Enable debug logging |
| `--help` | Show help |
| `--version` | Show version (2.0.0) |

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `ONTRACK_BACKEND` | Default matrix backend (overrides `--backend`) |
| `ONTRACK_SOLVER` | Default solver (overrides `--solver`) |
| `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` | Google Maps API key |
| `OSRM_BASE_URL` | OSRM server URL |

## Output Example

```
✓ 5 addresses loaded
✓ 5 stops after geocoding

✓ Route ready  5 stops  ·  42m 18s  ·  solver: TwoOpt  ·  matrix: osrm

   1.  123 Main St, Madison, WI
   2.  789 Pine Rd, Madison, WI
   3.  456 Oak Ave, Madison, WI
   4.  321 Elm St, Madison, WI
   5.  654 Maple Dr, Madison, WI

Google Maps:
  https://www.google.com/maps/dir/...
ArcGIS FieldMaps:
  https://fieldmaps.arcgis.com/...
```

## CSV Input Format

The input CSV needs an `address` column:

```csv
address
"123 Main St, Madison, WI"
"456 Oak Ave, Madison, WI"
```

Extra columns are ignored. If no header is detected, each line is treated as an address.
